Server takes 2 arguments wwith echo.c : PortNumber P      //PortNumber Refers to port to start server and P is Packet Size
Sample Call to server : ./echo 55555 100

Client takes 5 arguments ServerName PortNumber T P OutputFile //NameOfHost Port:must be same of server T:RC P:PacketSize OutputFileName 
Sample Call to client : ./client shivank-Inspiron-7348 55555 20 100 output1


